                <p class="text-slate-700 text-lg leading-relaxed"><strong>What certifications do chargers need for US and EU markets?</strong> For the US: FCC Part 15B (electromagnetic compliance) and UL 62368-1 (safety). For the EU: CE marking covering LVD, EMC, RoHS, and ErP directives. <strong>New for 2026:</strong> EU USB-C Universal Charger Directive requires USB Type-C and PD support for laptops by April 28, 2026. WOWOHCOOL holds all certifications and helps 200+ brands achieve <strong>98% first-pass certification</strong> success rate.</p>
